    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-10-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-10-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="620"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d620">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Chase</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward.</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Treasury Department</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-10-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 28, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor of acknowledging the receipt of
                    your communication of the 24th instant, relative to duties upon articles
                    furnished to foreign consuls in this country by their own governments for
                    official use.</p>
                <p>Your suggestion, “whether it may not be advisable that books, stationery, and
                    like articles, imported by foreign consuls resident in the United States, or
                    sent to them by their respective governments, and intended solely and entirely
                    for official use in their several consulates, be admitted free of duty,” is
                    worthy of consideration; and I will take early occasion to bring the subject to
                    the attention of Congress.</p>
                <p>With great respect, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>S. P. CHASE, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of the Treasury.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. W. H. <hi rend="smallcaps">Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of
                            State.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
